whereas.text:
Whereas, on February 3, 1863, Kansas became one of the
			 first States in the Nation to accept the terms and conditions of the First
			 Morrill Act creating the land-grant system of colleges and universities;

Whereas Kansas State University helped pioneer the
			 academic teaching of home economics for women becoming one of the first of two
			 colleges to offer the program of study;

Whereas Kansas State University has
			 expanded to campuses in Olathe and Salina, and its Research and Extension
			 program has strong presence throughout the State;

Whereas Kansas State University is a national leader among
			 public universities in Rhodes, Truman, Marshall, Udall, and Goldwater
			 scholars;
